h%20committee%2C%20said%20she's%20concerned%20clinicians%20will%20hold%20back%20in%20prescribing%20mifepristone%20and%20misoprostol%20where%20medically%20necessary%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-abortion-maternal-health-desert-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleave%20their%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20state%20entirely%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they're%20afraid%20of%20being%20jailed%20for%20providing%20adequate%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20were%20a%20doctor%2C%20I'd%20be%20thinking%2C%20now%20I've%20got%20Big%20Brother%20looking%20into%20how%20I'm%20practicing%20medicine%3F%20Why%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20medical%20care.%20We're%20already%20seeing%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abortion%20pills%20in%20bottles%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0mifepristone%20and%20misoprostol%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c9f6ec585f1dff88b16451%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222790%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Emifepristone%20and%20misoprostol%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FCharlie%20Neibergall%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20started%20funding%20states%20to%20set%20up%20PMPs%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20in%20response%20to%20the%20prescription%20opioid%20crisis.%20Most%20states%20now%20require%20doctors%20to%20check%20them%20before%20writing%20certain%20kinds%20of%20prescriptions.%20If%20a%20search%20shows%20that%20a%20patient%20is%20getting%20opioids%20from%20a%20laundry%20list%20of%20emergency%20rooms%2C%20that%20could%20be%20a%20sign%20that%20he's%20%26quot%3Bdoctor-shopping%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20misleading%20physicians%20for%20pills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20safeguard%20came%20with%20tradeoffs%3A%20If%20you've%20had%20a%20prescription%20for%20a%20controlled%20substance%20in%20your%20life%2C%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20can%20view%20it%20in%20your%20state%20database.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20health%20information%20is%20usually%20protected%20under%20the%20Health%20Insurance%20Portability%20and%20Accountability%20Act.%20But%20when%20controlled%20substance%20prescriptions%20are%20reported%20to%20the%20state%2C%20they%20lose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fwhat-is-hipaa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHIPAA%3C%2Fa%3E%20protections.%20Without%20those%20safeguards%2C%20third%20parties%20can%20access%20the%20data%20without%20patient%20consent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPMP%20access%20can%20extend%20to%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20groups%2C%20including%20state%20licensing%20boards%20and%20health%20departments%2C%20parole%20and%20probation%20agencies%2C%20and%20medical%20examiners%20and%20coroners.%20Under%20various%20conditions%2C%20law%20enforcement%20can%20also%20access%20the%20prescription%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20of%20drugs%20that%20PMPs%20monitor%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20details%20they%20collect%2C%20has%20steadily%20grown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20earliest%20PMPs%20collected%20limited%20patient%20information%2C%20and%20only%20about%20prescriptions%20with%20the%20highest%20risks%20of%20misuse%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffda-chief-approved-oxycontin-six-figure-gig-at-purdue-pharma-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoxycodone%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-fentanyl-crisis-mexico-canada-harm-reduction-expert-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efentanyl%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%202024%2C%20however%2C%2045%20states%20monitor%20all%20controlled%20substances%2C%20and%2037%20track%20%26quot%3Bdrugs%20of%20concern%2C%26quot%3B%20prescriptions%20that%20are%20not%20heavily%20regulated%20that%20the%20state%20deems%20risky%20for%20some%20individuals%2C%20according%20to%20research%20by%20health%20and%20law%20policy%20expert%20Jennifer%20Oliva.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20collected%20for%20each%20prescription%20is%20extensive%3A%20the%20drug's%20name%2C%20strength%2C%20quantity%2C%20and%20dispense%20date%3B%20the%20doctor's%20and%20pharmacist's%20DEA%20registration%20numbers%3B%20along%20with%20the%20patient's%20name%2C%20address%2C%20ZIP%20code%2C%20gender%2C%20date%20of%20birth%2C%20and%20driver's%20license.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222622%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20New%20York%20woman%20holds%20up%20a%20%23End%20Overdose%20blue%20sign%20at%20an%20International%20Overdose%20Awareness%20Day%20protest%20in%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ca063eb8b41a9673f9eac9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221967%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20International%20Overdose%20Awareness%20Day%20protest%20in%20New%20York%20in%202023.%20All%2050%20states%20have%20electronic%20PMPs%2C%20introduced%20largely%20to%20reduce%20overdoses%20from%20prescription%20opioids.%3Cp%3EErik%20McGregor%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EManaging%20this%20growing%20mountain%20of%20sensitive%20prescription%20data%20became%20a%20big%20business%20for%20Bamboo%20Health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBamboo%20was%20founded%20as%20Appriss%20in%201994%20in%20Louisville%2C%20Kentucky.%20Its%20first%20product%20was%20a%20data-aggregation%20and%20notification%20tool%20that%20informed%20victims%20when%20their%20offenders%20were%20released%20from%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tool%20became%20a%20%2430%20million%20business%20serving%2048%20states.%20The%20company's%20subsequent%20products%20helped%20law%20enforcement%20track%20sex%20offenders%20and%20monitor%20people%20who%20bought%20high%20quantities%20of%20Sudafed%20at%20pharmacies%2C%20which%20cops%20used%20to%20bust%20meth%20labs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20opioid%20crisis%20came%20to%20a%20head%2C%20Appriss%20was%20well-suited%20for%20the%20job.%20With%20its%20data%20prowess%20and%20close%20relationships%20with%20state%20governments%20%E2%80%94%20plus%20an%20early%20partnership%20with%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Boards%20of%20Pharmacy%2C%20which%20advises%20state%20PMP%20decision-makers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20gobbled%20up%20PMP%20contracts%20and%20cemented%20a%20dominant%20position%20in%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBamboo%20Health%20is%20now%20an%20independent%20company%20separated%20from%20other%20business%20lines%20built%20long%20ago%20under%20the%20Appriss%20name.%20Smith%2C%20the%20CEO%2C%20said%20Bamboo%20works%20with%2044%20US%20states%20and%20territories%20to%20facilitate%20more%20than%207%20billion%20prescription%20queries%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20PMPs%20earn%20money%20directly%20from%20states%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20hospitals%20themselves.%20Bamboo's%20PMP%20business%20makes%20up%20roughly%20half%20the%20company's%20revenue%2C%20according%20to%20a%20former%20employee%20with%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20matter.%20Altogether%2C%20Bamboo%20Health%20is%20bringing%20in%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20annually%2C%20per%20a%20February%20LinkedIn%20post%20by%20its%20recently%20departed%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20commercial%20revenue.%20Smith%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20company's%20financials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20has%20attracted%20large%20investors.%20Private%20equity%20firms%20Insight%20Partners%20and%20Clearlake%20Capital%20have%20backed%20Bamboo%20and%20sit%20on%20its%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20according%20to%20federal%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Appriss%20rebranded%20to%20Bamboo%20Health%20after%20buying%20PatientPing%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20collects%20data%20about%20patient%20admissions%2C%20discharges%2C%20and%20transfers%2C%20for%20about%20%24500%20million.%20The%20deal%20valued%20the%20combined%20company%20at%20more%20than%20%241.5%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vision%2C%20as%20Bamboo%20described%20it%2C%20was%20to%20combine%20the%20two%20companies'%20vast%20data%20feeds%20to%20equip%20providers%20with%20all%20the%20information%20they%20need%20during%20crucial%20moments%20of%20patient%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20PMPs%20have%20assisted%20regulators%20in%20busting%20pill-mill%20networks%20and%20curbing%20severe%20prescribing%20patterns.%20Bamboo%20even%20helped%20the%20feds%20hold%20pharmaceutical%20distributors%20accountable%20for%20their%20role%20in%20the%20opioid%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it's%20not%20clear%20that%20PMPs%20have%20reduced%20patient%20harm%20overall.%20One%20study%20showed%20that%20tools%20such%20as%20PMPs%20might%20increase%20heroin-related%20deaths%20as%20prescription%20opioid%20abusers%20switch%20to%20illicit%20drugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWired%20reported%20in%202021%20that%20a%20key%20Bamboo%20product%2C%20which%20displayed%20%26quot%3Boverdose%20risk%20scores%26quot%3B%20based%20on%20a%20patient's%20prescription%20history%2C%20was%20sometimes%20used%20to%20deny%20patients%20needed%20healthcare.%20Pharmacies%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20doctor's%20offices%20turned%20patients%20with%20high%20scores%20away%2C%20even%20when%20they%20had%20good%20reasons%20for%20taking%20opioids%2C%20such%20as%20endometriosis%2C%20a%20painful%2C%20chronic%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20former%20employees%20told%20BI%20that%20after%20the%20criticism%2C%20Bamboo%20prioritized%20updating%20the%20design%20of%20the%20scores%20to%20add%20more%20context%20and%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20point%20isn't%20to%20be%20the%20arbiter%20on%20who%20this%20person%20is%20and%20what%20they%20should%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20ex-staffers%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20to%20equip%20somebody%20with%20some%20information%20to%20make%20a%20better%20decision.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221962%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22appriss%20ceo%20mike%20davis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c9f75f585f1dff88b16466%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221472%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMike%20Davis%20cofounded%20Appriss%2C%20now%20Bamboo%20Health%2C%20and%20served%20as%20its%20CEO%20until%202020.%3Cp%3EAppriss%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBamboo's%20newest%20directive%20to%20monitor%20abortion%20medications%20may%20test%20this%20hands-off%20approach.%20Some%20employees%20worry%20that%20tracking%20these%20drugs%20will%20harm%20doctors%20and%20patients%2C%20rather%20than%20advancing%20the%20company's%20goal%20of%20improving%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProviding%20monitoring%20of%20mifepristone%20and%20misoprostol%2C%20in%20support%20of%20limiting%20the%20use%20of%20and%20access%20to%20those%20drugs%2C%20is%20acting%20in%20direct%20contradiction%20of%20that%20mission%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20former%20employee%20who%20was%20working%20at%20Bamboo%20when%20the%20company%20internally%20announced%20plans%20to%20monitor%20the%20drugs.%20The%20person%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20because%20they%20were%20not%20authorized%20by%20Bamboo%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20dangerous%20thing%20when%20a%20healthcare%20company%20is%20not%20making%20decisions%20based%20on%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20patient%2C%20but%20on%2C%20perhaps%2C%20opportunities%20for%20near-term%20revenue%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20how%20Bamboo%20has%20responded%20to%20employee%20pushback%20about%20the%20company%20monitoring%20abortion%20pill%20prescriptions%20in%20Louisiana%2C%20Smith%20said%20as%20Bamboo%20has%20expanded%20its%20focus%20to%20patients%20with%20high-need%20conditions%20in%20areas%20like%20behavioral%20health%2C%20it's%20sought%20out%20new%20employees%20with%20expertise%20in%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20important%20that%20we%20have%20the%20right%20people%20on%20the%20team%20to%20help%20us%20execute%20on%20that%20vision%20and%20mission%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNot%20everybody's%20going%20to%20be%20on%20the%20same%20page%2C%20as%20we%20look%20to%20expand%20our%20charter%20and%20where%20we're%20going.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20have%20aggressively%20enforced%20abortion%20bans%2C%20putting%20new%20pressure%20on%20some%20doctors.%20Texas%20and%20Louisiana%20have%20sued%20and%20indicted%20at%20least%20one%20doctor%20for%20prescribing%20abortion%20pills%20to%20state%20residents%20via%20telehealth%20services.%20Idaho%20and%20Texas%20let%20private%20citizens%20sue%20virtually%20anyone%20who%20performs%20or%20assists%20with%20an%20abortion.%20These%20so-called%20bounty-hunter%20laws%20award%20%2410%2C000%20or%20more%20to%20successful%20plaintiffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20states%20will%20be%20even%20more%20emboldened%20to%20use%20all%20the%20tools%20at%20their%20disposal%20to%20restrict%20access%2C%20Randi%20Seigel%2C%20a%20lawyer%20specializing%20in%20healthcare%20at%20the%20firm%20Manatt%2C%20Phelps%20%26amp%3B%20Phillips%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPregnant%20individuals%20in%20Louisiana%20are%20not%20subject%20to%20criminal%20prosecution%20for%20obtaining%20and%20using%20these%20drugs%20for%20self-managed%20abortions.%20But%20the%20doctors%20and%20pharmacists%20involved%20are%20another%20story.%20In%20these%20cases%2C%20somebody%20who's%20suspicious%20about%20why%20a%20patient%20was%20given%20mifepristone%20could%20report%20it%20to%20law%20enforcement%20and%20trigger%20an%20investigation.%20Officials%20could%20then%20seek%20access%20to%20PMP%20data%20for%20that%20investigation%2C%20per%20Seigel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbortion%20regulations%20are%20already%20getting%20in%20the%20way%20of%20necessary%20medical%20care%3A%20Several%20women%20have%20died%20from%20preventable%20complications%20after%20they%20couldn't%20access%20timely%20treatment%20in%20states%20with%20abortion%20bans%2C%20ProPublica%20has%20reported.%20Although%20certain%20legal%20exceptions%20are%20supposed%20to%20protect%20the%20life%20of%20the%20mother%2C%20some%20doctors%20may%20wait%20too%20long%20to%20intervene%20out%20of%20fear%20that%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eif%20the%20patient%20isn't%20clearly%20dying%2C%20their%20use%20of%20the%20drugs%20could%20be%20questioned%2C%20Seigel%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20concerned%20that%20tracking%20misoprostol%20and%20mifepristone%20prescriptions%20could%20have%20a%20similar%20effect%20on%20doctors'%20decisions.%20If%20doctors%20are%20concerned%20they%20may%20be%20accused%20of%20triggering%20an%20abortion%20while%20providing%20legal%20and%20medically%20necessary%20services%2C%20they%20might%20delay%20giving%20that%20care%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20could%20imagine%20somebody%20coming%20in%20who's%20having%20a%20miscarriage%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20is%20appropriate%20for%20miscarriage%20management%20%E2%80%94%20and%20somebody%20saying%2C%20'Well%2C%20wait%2C%20we%20have%20to%20wait%20a%20little%20longer%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20are%20really%20having%20a%20miscarriage%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Louisiana%2C%20which%20has%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20maternal%20mortality%20rates%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20new%20regulations%20are%20already%20causing%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faspiring-obgyns-worried-about-adequate-training-post-roe-v-wade-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobstetrician-gynecologists%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20carried%20misoprostol%20in%20their%20pockets%20for%20emergencies.%20Now%2C%20the%20medicine%20must%20be%20stored%20in%20locked%20cabinets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvegno%20told%20BI%20that%20clinicians%20across%20Louisiana%20have%20been%20running%20%26quot%3Btime%20trials%26quot%3B%20to%20test%20how%20quickly%20they%20can%20retrieve%20misoprostol%20from%20those%20locked%20cabinets%2C%20bring%20it%20back%20to%20the%20patient%2C%20and%20administer%20it.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20severe%20postpartum%20hemorrhaging%2C%20mere%20minutes%20could%20be%20the%20difference%20between%20life%20and%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222830%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Louisiana%20governor%20Jeff%20Landry%20signed%20the%20first%20bill%20of%20its%20kind%20to%20make%20mifepristone%20and%20misoprostol%20controlled%20substances%20in%20May%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ca05edb8b41a9673f9eaab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222123%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELouisiana%20Gov.%20Jeff%20Landry%20signed%20the%20state's%20law%2C%20the%20first%20of%20its%20kind%2C%20to%20make%20mifepristone%20and%20misoprostol%20controlled%20substances%20in%20May%202024.%3Cp%3EChris%20Maddaloni%2FCQ%20Roll%20Call%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20outpatient%20pharmacies%20have%20decided%20to%20stop%20stocking%20the%20pills%20altogether%2C%20Avegno%20added.%20Others%20are%20going%20beyond%20what's%20required%20by%20the%20law%2C%20including%20calling%20doctors%20to%20confirm%20what%20they've%20written%20on%20the%20prescriptions%2C%20slowing%20down%20access%20for%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20pharmacists%20are%20often%20confused%20about%20the%20law%20and%20afraid%20of%20liability%2C%20Avegno%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20fill%20this%20prescription%20and%20somebody%20uses%20it%20to%20secretly%20have%20an%20abortion%2C%20am%20I%20going%20to%20be%20held%20liable%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20introduction%20of%20mifepristone%20and%20misoprostol%20monitoring%20via%20Bamboo's%20database%20could%20add%20to%20that%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20say%20I'm%20an%20OB.%20I%20have%20a%20busy%20clinic.%20I'm%20putting%20in%20IUDs%20all%20the%20time%2C%20I'm%20managing%20miscarriages%2C%20and%20I'm%20doing%20hysteroscopies%2C%20all%20of%20which%20might%20require%20me%20to%20write%20m