hat%20he%20gave%20every%20batch%20of%20interns%20at%20the%20company.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20thread%20on%20X%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Shear%20said%20that%20he'd%20give%20each%20intern%20batch%20a%20presentation%20on%20Twitch's%20origins%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20Q%26amp%3BA%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20one%20question%20he%20was%20always%20asked%20during%20Q%26amp%3BA%20was%3A%20%26quot%3BWhere%20should%20I%20work%20and%20what%20job%20should%20I%20get%2C%20or%20should%20I%20start%20a%20company%3F%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20varies%20from%20person%20to%20person%2C%20Shear%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20outlined%20his%20advice%20and%20the%20thought%20process%20behind%20it%20in%20his%20X%20thread.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20an%20interesting%20question%20to%20try%20to%20answer%20for%20an%20intern%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20really%20know%2C%20because%20of%20course%20the%20actual%20answer%20is%20dependent%20on%20that%20person%20and%20their%20life.%20So%20I%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20articulate%20the%20framework%20I%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Emmett%20Shear%20(%40eshear)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Feshear%2Fstatus%2F1898576024331505904%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%209%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20pursue%20careers%20for%20different%20reasons%2C%20such%20as%20money%2C%20prestige%2C%20power%2C%20and%20advancement%20opportunities%2C%20Shear%20wrote.%20But%20there%20were%20downsides%20to%20each%20of%20these%20reasons%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoney%20is%20a%20top%20reason%2C%20Shear%20wrote%2C%20but%20has%20%26quot%3Bdiminishing%20returns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrestige%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bmostly%20a%20trap%2C%20for%20the%20same%20reason%20designer%20clothing%20brands%20are%20bad%20deals%2C%26quot%3B%20Shear%20said.%20While%20a%20prestigious%20job%20%26quot%3Bmight%20make%20some%20less%20discerning%20people%20think%20better%20of%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20will%20not%20%26quot%3Bactually%20make%20you%20better%20or%20better%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShear%20added%20that%20jobs%20promising%20power%20only%20offer%20you%20%26quot%3Bborrowed%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20especially%20if%20one%20has%20just%20begun%20their%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20if%20they're%20pitching%20you%20on%20power%20it's%20usually%20a%20trick%20of%20some%20kind.%20They're%20trying%20to%20convince%20you%20to%20accept%20less%20compensation%20in%20other%20ways%20by%20offering%20a%20mirage%2C%26quot%3B%20Shear%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShear%20said%20some%20people%20may%20be%20attracted%20to%20%26quot%3Btracked%20jobs%26quot%3B%20that%20offer%20advancement%20opportunities%2C%20like%20becoming%20partners%20at%20a%20law%20firm.%20Such%20jobs%20may%20work%20for%20people%20who%20enjoy%20competing%20with%20their%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20people%20could%20pick%20careers%20based%20on%20the%20work%20itself%2C%20Shear%20said.%20Work%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bintrinsically%20rewarding%26quot%3B%20when%20one%20learns%20and%20grows%20at%20their%20job%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20growth%20makes%20workers%20%26quot%3Bmore%20valuable%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Shear%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20choosing%20one's%20career%20path%20comes%20down%20to%20knowing%20yourself%2C%20Shear%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20in%20general%20it%20seems%20clear%20ppl%20should%20satisfice%20for%20cash%2C%20optimize%20for%20learning%2Fgrowth%2C%20and%20ignore%20everything%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Shear%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20love%20economy-sized%20pain%20and%20feel%20like%20you%20have