fforts%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-performance-cuts-mark-zuckerberg-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraise%20the%20bar%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20on%20performance%2C%20as%20Zuckerberg%20put%20it%2C%20tend%20to%20backfire%20with%20remarkable%20consistency.%20CEOs%20may%20%3Cem%3Ethink%3C%2Fem%3E%20they're%20creating%20a%20meritocracy%2C%20but%20in%20reality%20they're%20marching%20their%20companies%20straight%20into%20a%20trap%20of%20sunken%20morale%2C%20high%20turnover%2C%20depressed%20profits%2C%20and%20reduced%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20short%20run%2C%20you%20might%20be%20creating%20some%20heightened%20performance%20standards%20and%20some%20accountability%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Grant%2C%20who%20serves%20as%20the%20chief%20work-life%20expert%20at%20Glassdoor.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20you%20may%20be%20shooting%20your%20organization%20in%20the%20foot.%26quot%3B%20The%20evidence%20on%20making%20employees%20fear%20for%20their%20jobs%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20is%20clear%3A%20%26quot%3BThey're%20very%20shortsighted%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20motivates%20workers%20to%20do%20their%20best%3F%20It's%20a%20question%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-manager-hiring-white-collar-recession-layoffs-jobs-efficiency-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20wrestling%20with%20for%20as%20long%20as%20managers%20have%20been%20around.%20Back%20when%20America%20was%20first%20industrializing%2C%20the%20prevailing%20belief%20was%20that%20the%20best%20tool%20for%20driving%20employees%20was%20fear.%20The%20influential%20management%20theorist%20Frederick%20Taylor%20argued%20that%20workers%20were%20inherently%20lazy%20and%20in%20need%20of%20constant%20supervision.%20Swooping%20into%20factories%2C%20he%20set%20brutally%20high%20productivity%20standards%20%E2%80%94%20and%20summarily%20fired%20anyone%20who%20fell%20short.%20Everyone%20else%20had%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20buckle%20down%20and%20grind%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20unsafe%20the%20new%20standards%20might%20be%2C%20or%20how%20much%20misery%20they%20provoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Taylorism%20swept%20the%20country%2C%20it%20made%20things%20worse%20rather%20than%20better%2C%20contributing%20to%20a%20wave%20of%20strikes%20that%20left%20factories%20idle%20for%20long%20stretches.%20By%20the%201950s%2C%20many%20companies%20were%20trying%20out%20a%20kinder%2C%20gentler%20philosophy%20of%20management.%20Instead%20of%20using%20fear%20to%20drive%20workers%2C%20they%20drew%20on%20a%20host%20of%20other%20motivating%20forces%20identified%20by%20organizational%20psychologists%3A%20a%20sense%20of%20connection%20and%20community%2C%20interesting%20and%20varied%20tasks%2C%20the%20desire%20to%20be%20useful.%20But%20in%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20as%20globalization%20began%20to%20erode%20American%20competitiveness%2C%20management%20by%20fear%20came%20roaring%20back.%20At%20General%20Electric%2C%20Jack%20Welch%20famously%20ordered%20his%20managers%20to%20rank%2020%25%20of%20their%20employees%20as%20A%20players%2C%2070%25%20as%20B%20players%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20remaining%2010%25%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20were%20fired%20for%20low%20performance%2C%20as%20C%20players.%20The%20practice%2C%20which%20came%20to%20be%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Brank%20and%20yank%2C%26quot%3B%20spread%20throughout%20corporate%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20management%20philosophy%2C%20it%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20disaster.%20Take%20what%20happened%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20where%20the%20rank-and-yank%20system%20was%20known%20by%20another%20name%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstack-ranking-employees-is-a-bad-idea-2013-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estack%20ranking%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20the%20once%20dominant%20company%20had%20watched%20its%20market%20cap%20plunge%20by%20more%20than%2050%25.%20One%20of%20the%20primary%20culprits%3F%20Its%20Welchian%20management%20system%2C%20which%20treated%20performance%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-is-filled-with-abusive-managers-and-overworked-employees-says-tell-all-book-2012-5%3Fop%3D1%23the-myth-of-the-fabulous-stock-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20zero-sum%20game%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you%20wanted%20to%20succeed%2C%20someone%20else%20had%20to%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStaffers%20were%20rewarded%20not%20just%20for%20doing%20well%20but%20for%20making%20sure%20that%20their%20colleagues%20failed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20journalist%20Kurt%20Eichenwald%20found.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20company%20was%20consumed%20by%20an%20endless%20series%20of%20internal%20knife%20fights.%20Potential%20market-busting%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20e-book%20and%20smartphone%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20were%20killed%2C%20derailed%2C%20or%20delayed%20amid%20bickering%20and%20power%20plays.%26quot%3B%20By%202013%2C%20when%20Microsoft%20finally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-just-killed-its-controversial-stack-ranking-employee-review-system-2013-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabandoned%20stack%20ranking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20much%20of%20corporate%20America%20had%20as%20well%20%E2%80%94%20including%20GE%2C%20where%20it%20all%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20long%20history%20of%20management%20by%20fear%20has%20given%20scholars%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20to%20scrutinize.%20So%20what%20has%20all%20the%20research%20found%3F%20For%20starters%2C%20using%20terror%20to%20motivate%20your%20staff%20works%20in%20the%20short%20run%3A%20When%20their%20jobs%20are%20hanging%20in%20the%20balance%2C%20employees%20work%20harder%20and%20faster.%20But%20the%20initial%20surge%20in%20productivity%2C%20studies%20have%20shown%2C%20comes%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20%3Cem%3Equality%3C%2Fem%3E.%20As%20workers%20rush%20to%20keep%20up%2C%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Fbuy%2F2002-01632-002%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutput%20is%20inevitably%20shoddier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20riddled%20with%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20work%20in%20the%20performance%20pressure%20cooker%20becomes%20less%20innovative.%20Take%20a%20study%20that%20took%20place%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20at%20a%20Fortune%20500%20tech%20company%20with%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20employees.%20After%20a%20series%20of%20layoffs%2C%20the%20remaining%20high%20performers%20became%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdash.lib.harvard.edu%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F1%2F37940231%2FDownsizing-changes-in-the-work-environment-for-creativity-Amabile-Conti-1999.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20creative%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20generated%20fewer%20new%20ideas%20for%20inventions.%20Organizational%20psychologists%20call%20this%20a%20%26quot%3Bthreat-rigidity%20response%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20our%20tendency%20to%20respond%20to%20fear%20by%20clinging%20to%20the%20familiar.%20The%20anxiety%20generated%20by%20job%20insecurity%20becomes%20so%20overwhelming%2C%20studies%20suggest%2C%20that%20it%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FSusan-Stewart-16%2Fpublication%2F227783864_Productivity_Counterproductivity_and_Creativity_The_Ups_and_Downs_of_Job_Insecurity%2Flinks%2F611d6ab51e95fe241adfccdc%2FProductivity-Counterproductivity-and-Creativity-The-Ups-and-Downs-of-Job-Insecurity.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpairs%20people's%20cognitive%20functioning%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20might%20not%20matter%20so%20much%20when%20you're%20completing%20routine%20tasks%2C%20but%20it's%20debilitating%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20problem-solving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20focus%20very%20narrowly%20on%20protecting%20their%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Grant.%20%26quot%3BThey%20stop%20taking%20risks%20and%20thinking%20creatively%20and%20innovating%2C%20which%20is%20exactly%20what%20you%20need%20them%20to%20do%20in%20a%20turbulent%20environment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20employees%20fear%20for%20their%20job%20security%20also%20causes%20them%20to%20flee%3A%20One%20study%20estimated%20that%20laying%20off%20just%201%25%20of%20a%20workforce%20would%2C%20on%20average%2C%20lead%20to%20a%2031%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FCharlie-Trevor%2Fpublication%2F211395271_Keeping_Your_Headcount_When_All_About_You_Are_Losing_Theirs_Downsizing_Voluntary_Turnover_Rates_and_The_Moderating_Role_of_HR_Practices%2Flinks%2F0f317539b2284c8a3b000000%2FKeeping-Your-Headcount-When-All-About-You-Are-Losing-Theirs-Downsizing-Voluntary-Turnover-Rates-and-The-Moderating-Role-of-HR-Practices.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espike%20in%20voluntary%20turnover%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20might%20not%20sound%20so%20terrible%20for%20a%20company%20that's%20trimming%20its%20head%20count%2C%20but%20the%20departures%20aren't%20random.%20High%20performers%2C%20who%20have%20the%20most%20options%2C%20leave%20in%20far%20larger%20numbers%20than%20mediocre%20employees.%20Creating%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-today-tech-jobs-anxiety-zirp-careers-layoffs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eculture%20of%20fear%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20makes%20it%20harder%20to%20recruit%20high%20performers.%20In%20one%20study%2C%20businesses%20that%20conducted%20layoffs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fciteseerx.ist.psu.edu%2Fdocument%3Frepid%3Drep1%26type%3Dpdf%26doi%3D68ccbb559e86ea445c83696a4e8279e4ae02958e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Fortune's%20rankings%20of%20the%20most%20admired%20companies.%20The%20more%20you%20slash%20your%20low%20performers%2C%20the%20fewer%20high%20performers%20you'll%20wind%20up%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPretty%20much%20every%20study%20that%20has%20ever%20crunched%20the%20numbers%20has%20found%20the%20same%20thing%3A%20Contrary%20to%20what%20leaders%20li