rstones%20of%20good%20management%20today.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20some%20companies%20may%20have%20swung%20a%20little%20too%20far%20to%20the%20gentle%20side%2C%20suspending%20performance%20reviews%20altogether.%20It%20was%20an%20expression%20of%20empathy%20that%20recognized%20the%20extraordinary%20stresses%20of%20the%20crisis%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20left%20some%20managers%20with%20no%20idea%20what%20their%20employees%20were%20doing%2C%20let%20alone%20how%20well%20they%20were%20doing%20it.%20High%20performers%20weren't%20getting%20recognized%20and%20rewarded%2C%20and%20low%20performers%20weren't%20getting%20the%20help%20they%20needed.%20Many%20bosses%20blamed%20the%20chaos%20on%20remote%20work%2C%20and%20ordered%20everyone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eback%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20real%20problem%20was%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20properly%20functioning%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-performance-evaluations-management-reviews-promotions-raises%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esystem%20of%20performance%20management%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20big%20difference%20between%20being%20demanding%20and%20being%20demeaning%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Grant.%20%26quot%3BDemanding%20is%20about%20saying%3A%20'Look%2C%20we%20have%20extremely%20high%20expectations.%20We%20hired%20you%20because%20we%20believe%20you're%20capable%20of%20meeting%20them.%20Here%20are%20your%20goals.%20Let's%20talk%20through%20what%20I%20can%20do%20to%20help%20you%20achieve%20them.'%20Then%2C%20if%20somebody%20is%20not%20pulling%20their%20weight%2C%20you%20give%20them%20feedback%20%E2%80%94%20you%20let%20them%20know%20what%20they%20need%20to%20change.%20If%20they're%20not%20willing%20or%20able%20to%20change%20it%2C%20yes%2C%20of%20course%2C%20at%20some%20point%20you%20let%20them%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demeaning%20way%3F%20It's%20basically%20the%20approach%20being%20taken%20by%20Zuckerberg%20and%20Musk.%20Setting%20arbitrary%20quotas%20of%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20who%20should%20get%20cut.%20Forcing%20managers%20to%20fire%20people%20who%20were%20consistently%20told%20they%20were%20meeting%20and%20exceeding%20expectations.%20Publicly%20labeling%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Blow%20performers%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20hurts%20their%20chances%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elanding%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20above%20all%2C%20failing%20to%20recognize%20that%20an%20employee%20who%20isn't%20working%20out%20isn't%20just%20a%20failure%20of%20the%20individual.%20It's%20also%20a%20failure%20of%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%26quot%3B%20Grant%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20vogue%20right%20now%20is%20a%20more%20demeaning%20approach%20to%20leadership.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20overwhelming%20evidence%20against%20management%20by%20fear%2C%20it's%20puzzling%20why%20Silicon%20Valley%20is%20trying%20to%20revive%20it.%20The%20tech%20industry%2C%20after%20all%2C%20was%20founded%20on%20the%20belief%20that%20everything%20should%20be%20dictated%20by%20data.%20Grant%20blames%20ignorance.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20talk%20with%20CEOs%2C%20many%20of%20them%20are%20just%20unaware%20of%20the%20evidence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey%20haven't%20thought%20through%20the%20unintended%20consequences%20of%20their%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurely%2C%20though%2C%20it%20shouldn't%20be%20difficult%20for%20a%20company%20like%20Microsoft%20to%20remember%20just%20how%20poorly%20things%20went%20the%20last%20time%20it%20went%20after%20low%20performers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20much%20better%20it%20did%20once%20it%20replaced%20stack%20ranking%20with%20Satya%20Nadella's%20softer%20approach%20of%20%26quot%3Bmodel%2C%20coach%2C%20care.%26quot%3B%20Microsoft%20post-2013%20is%20one%20of%20the%20great%20success%20stories%20of%20the%20past%20decade%20%E2%80%94%20an%20ailing%20giant%20that%20actually%20managed%20to%20become%20relevant%20again.%20The%20tech%20industry%20boomed%2C%20in%20no%20small%20part%2C%20because%20starry-eyed%20startups%20motivated%20their%20coders%20and%20product%20managers%20and%20salespeople%20with%20the%20promise%20that%20they%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanging%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Eager%20millennials%20were%20happy%20to%20devote%20their%20nights%20and%20weekends%20to%20make%20that%20mission%20a%20reality%2C%20and%20they%20turned%20their%20underdog%20employers%20into%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20businesses%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hugely%20frustrating%2C%20because%20we%20become%20smart%20for%20a%20while%20and%20then%20we%20become%20stupid%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sucher%2C%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20professor.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you've%20been%20in%20business%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20which%20I%20have%20now%2C%20you%20get%20used%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20goes%20in%20cycles%20like%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20using%20performance-based%20cuts%20to%20instill%20fear%20in%20their%20employees%20is%20just%20the%20CEO%20version%20of%20a%20threat-rigidity%20response.%20In%20the%201980s%2C%20the%20threat%20was%20global%20competition.%20Today%2C%20it's%20the%20winner-takes-all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarc-benioff-salesforce-microsoft-big-tech-ai-spending-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewar%20over%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Under%20siege%2C%20history%20teaches%20us%2C%20bosses%20behave%20the%20same%20way%20employees%20do%3A%20They%20keep%20reverting%20to%20the%20same%20tired%20methods%20that%20just%20don't%20work%2C%20no